        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(i18n): add Hebrew (he) locale",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw had no Hebrew (`he`) locale. Hebrew users got the English Control UI and no Hebrew docs.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nRegisters `he` end-to-end and ships real generated Hebrew so Hebrew is a first-class, fully-translated locale like every other supported one.\n\n## User Impact\n\n- Hebrew appears in the Control UI language switcher and loads as a lazy locale bundle.\n- Browser language `he` (and legacy `iw`) auto-resolves to Hebrew.\n- Hebrew strings render correctly (RTL text); existing `detectTextDirection` already handles the Hebrew script.\n- Docs translation is wired: `he` registered in `scripts/docs-sync-publish.mjs` `GENERATED_LOCALES` (Mintlify accepts `he` in `navigation.languages`, so it shows in the docs picker).\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Real translations (addresses the prior \"fallback-only\" block):**\n- `ui/src/i18n/locales/he.ts` regenerated via the standard generator — `he.meta.json` reports `translatedKeys: 1414` of `1414` (0 fallbacks).\n- `he` added to the fallback-bundle regression guard in `ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts` (now enforced for Hebrew).\n\n**Wiring:** `ui/src/i18n/lib/types.ts`, `registry.ts` (lazy loader + `resolveNavigatorLocale` incl. legacy `iw`), `scripts/control-ui-i18n.ts`, `control-ui-i18n-report.ts`, language label in `en.ts`, CI matrix in `.github/workflows/control-ui-locale-refresh.yml`, docs `GENERATED_LOCALES` + `docs/.i18n/glossary.he.json` + `he-navigation.json`.\n\n**Checks:**\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check` → `he: clean (fallbacks=0)`.\n- `ui/src/i18n/test/translate.test.ts` → 11/11 passing.\n- `test/scripts/docs-sync-publish.test.ts` → 2/2 passing.\n- `pnpm --dir ui build` → succeeds; emits separate `he-*.js` chunk.\n\n**Real behavior proof (built Control UI, headless Chromium):**\n- Browser-locale `he-IL` auto-selects Hebrew; the connect screen renders Hebrew: `לוח בקרה של Gateway`, `כתובת URL של WebSocket`, `אסימון Gateway`, `התחבר`, and the Hebrew \"cannot connect\" guidance.\n- Explicit locale selection (`openclaw.i18n.locale=he`) renders the same Hebrew UI.\n- Screenshot attached below.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "feat/i18n-hebrew-locale",
